DOC.TE:
   Who are these scavengers, these people watching the runners not
for the race but to pick up what they leave behind? The homeless,
mostly, or those working on their behalf.

   Public buildings have been adorned with giant canopies of red,
white and blue; street medians are decorated with flag-like bunting;
and handkerchief-size standards wave from automobiles everywhere.

   House of Victorian Visions Bridal Museum, 254 S. Glassell, Orange;
(714) 997-1893; open Wednesday to Saturday, 11 a.m. to 6 p.m.;
www.victorianbridalmuseum.com.

DOC.LD:
Bill Slavin wanted something out of the ordinary to hang inside his
new cabin in Alabama. An Alaska grizzly bear would be ideal, he decided;
it would exude the mystique of the wild far north.

DOC.TE:
   Arizona State locked up Arizona defensively in the second half;
the Wildcats (14-14) made only four of 23 shots in the last 20
minutes.
